The paper deals with a distributed averaging problem in a network, which involves communication and local processing. This suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of protocols and algorithms, which could place it in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents theoretical results and establishes bounds, which could suggest that it belongs to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
